Package com.uniswdc.api.core

Interface Summary
Connection Represents a logical connection to a storage domain.You can create a Connection object by calling one of the static getConnection methods on the Factory.Connection class.
ContentTransfer Represents content data that is local to an object store and directly managed by the Content Engine server.
Document Represents a single version of a document stored in an object store.
Domain Represents a collection of resources and services.Currently, it is empty for being compatible with filenet.
Folder Represents a container that can hold other Containable subclasses, but cannot have content data of its own.
IndependentlyPersistableObject Represents a persistable IndependentObject that you can directly create, update, and delete.
ObjectStore Represents a location in which folders, documents, and custom objects are stored, accessed.
